      "description": "This 996.2-generation Carrera represents a mechanically sound example of the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus. Power is delivered through a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle, offering exceptional tactile feedback. The chassis retains its composure via a multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson front struts, providing the signature rear-engine weight bias and turn-in precision. Crucially, this unit has undergone a preemptive IMS bearing retrofit and Rear Main Seal (RMS) replacement, mitigating common failure points. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with its mileage, the powertrain remains robust with consistent compression across all cylinders and a linear torque curve. Ideal for the purist seeking a sorted, high-performance driver.",
